their coverage and company rates rather than having an agent sell you why not find which carrier is best for your business and approach them contact us to see if there is a better fit for your business we are not insurance agents and are not trying to sell you anything we will simply tell you some carriers that may be better suited and suggest agents in your area close ×close what is an experience mod rating the mod rating is one of the two most important factors that effect a carriers premium for workers comp insurance each business in a state is provided a mod rating by the states rating bureau which is a reflection of the amount of workers comp claims they have had if someone has an accident at work your mod rating will increase and so will your premium close ×close what is an lcm a loss cost multiplier or lcm is a rating for an insurance carrier that reflects their overhead in providing coverage for workers comp insurance it is one of the two main ratings that effect an insurance premium you are more likely to get a better premium from a carrier with a lower lcm so it is important to know what your carriers lcm is while a premium is generally the result of a formula carriers are able to deviate plus or minus  from that formula close try it location county state arizona colorado connecticut delaware florida georgia illinois maryland michigan north carolina new jersey nevada new york ohio pennsylvania south carolina tennessee texas within of policy info range effective dates to class code   farmnursery employees and dri   farm gardeningmarket or truc   farm orchard  drivers   farm poultry or egg producer   farm florist  drivers   farm dairy  drivers   farm field crops  drivers   landscape gardening  drivers   farm machinery operationby co           farm berry or vineyard  driv   farm cattle or livestock rais   tree pruning spraying repair   farm fish hatchery  drivers   farm animal raising  drivers   irrigation works operation  d       domestic workersinsideoccasi